title.narrative: ECD AND SCHOOL READINESS

description.narrative: By 2018, 50% of children aged 4-8 benefit from integrated Early Child Development (ECD) services at community or centre level., which contributes to Early Childhood Development, Early Learning, Learning Outcomes. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By the end of 2018, 66% of school-aged children (boys and girls) (especially among the socially excluded), benefit from continued access to improved learning through to secondary education within a safe schooling environment.
